Working with classes
div.classList.add('new');                                      
// adds class "new" to your new div

div.classList.remove('new');                                   
// remove "new" class from div

div.classList.toggle('active');                                
// if div doesn't have class "active" then add it, or if
// it does, then remove it
It is often standard (and more clean) to toggle a CSS style rather than adding and removing inline CSS.

Adding text content
div.textContent = 'Hello World!'                               
// creates a text node containing "Hello World!" and
// inserts it in div


Adding HTML content
div.innerHTML = '<span>Hello World!</span>';                   
// renders the html inside div

*Note that textContent is preferable for adding text, and innerHTML should be used sparingly as it can create 
security risks if misused.

